Summary: This section explains how to use motion sensors (gyroscope and accelerometer) on game controllers in Godot.

Motion sensors (gyroscope and accelerometer) allow games to track the controller's physical rotation and movement. This can be used for features like controlling the in-game camera by moving the controller or performing special actions by shaking it.

Several controller brands, notably PlayStation and Nintendo, include motion sensors in their modern controllers. Xbox controllers do not have these sensors.

To check if a connected controller has motion sensors, use Input.has_joy_motion_sensors().

Motion sensors are disabled by default to conserve controller battery life. To enable them, call Input.set_joy_motion_sensors_enabled().

The axes of the values reported by controller motion sensors are always relative to the controller's natural orientation.

The controller's gyroscope values indicate rotation around their respective axes:
- X value: rotation around the X axis (roll).
- Y value: rotation around the Y axis (yaw).
- Z value: rotation around the Z axis (pitch).

The controller's accelerometer provides values for movement along its axes:
- +X and -X: Movement left and right.
- +Y and -Y: Movement down and up.
- +Z and -Z: Movement away from and towards the user.
---CHUNK---
